  "title": "Mechanical Technician (Pharma)",
  "description": "<p><strong>Job scope:</strong></p><ul><li>Carry out maintenance activities in accordance with established procedures, good engineering practices, and cGMP requirements.</li><li>Perform preventive and predictive maintenance on plant equipment and facilities to ensure high reliability and maximum uptime.</li><li>Assist in the development of preventive maintenance SOPs, procedures, and tasks to support effective asset management.</li><li>Troubleshoot equipment issues by observing operations, listening for abnormalities, and using appropriate measuring and testing instruments to identify root causes.</li><li>Participate in continuous improvement initiatives and support IRS/QAR investigations.</li><li>Support project construction and commissioning activities by actively participating in punch listing and commissioning; collaborate with supervisors and engineers on equipment improvements and modifications.</li><li>Ensure a safe, organized, and clean work environment within assigned areas of responsibility.</li></ul><p></p>",
